      {
        "id": "8d3088bfa93522f39af7337639ad7b97aaeb9802",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 481,
          "name": "Jessica Wagantall",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jwagantall@linuxfoundation.org",
          "username": "jwagantall"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-10-09 16:10:48.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\nIn my opinion, moving CLM and IQ from master to casablanca will cause the reports history to become quite unreliable. \n\nIdeally, teams should run these jobs in master and fix on all branches since neither tools have a good understanding of \"branches\" and will generate confusing history in the reports. \n\nGildas, what do you think?",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "ac620ecba8392b837cfde0f9c5488fb6202a48f9",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 75,
          "name": "Venkata Harish Kajur",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "vk250x@att.com",
          "username": "vk250x"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-10-09 16:26:01.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n@Jessica, the only reason this was done because potentially there could be changes happening for dublin and that could impact the nexus iq scans and shouldn't the nexus iq scans be dependent on the casablanca branch right so that way it will only be one branch and once casablanca is released we can switch this back to master.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "ad536863c07891bb694ec1b9e3c11908ffe47da6",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 481,
          "name": "Jessica Wagantall",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jwagantall@linuxfoundation.org",
          "username": "jwagantall"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-10-09 16:53:22.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nSwitching branches can potentially affect the trend of the scans, as far as I know. As long as you guys are ok with that, I can merge this.\nIs that ok?",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "e487ee3ba78c34a72a2cc297cc6afe3be894b661",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 33,
          "name": "James Forsyth",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jf2512@att.com",
          "username": "jimmydot"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-10-09 17:27:01.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nWe are OK with it, and we'll move it back to master as soon as Casablanca is released and we need to start tracking Dublin.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
